<Lessons Title="Introduction to the Keyboard Layout">
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 1. Home Row - Right Hand</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>On your main keyboard, find the third row from the bottom. This row is the Home row. On this row, you will find two special keys with a bump on each key: the F key on the left and the J key on the right. Put your right index finger on the J key, then on the right next to it, put your right middle finger on the K key, your ring finger on the L key and your pinky finger on the Semi-colon key. Your right thumb should be on the Space bar on the first row from the bottom. The Space bar is the longest key on the keyboard.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType>#j|k|l|;| </TextToType>
		<LessonTime>2</LessonTime>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<KeysToType/>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 2. Home Row - Left Hand</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>On your main keyboard, find the third row from the bottom. This row is the Home row. On this row, you will find two special keys with a bump on each key: the F key on the left and the J key on the right. Put your left index finger on the F key, then on the left next to it, put your left middle finger on the D key, your ring finger on the S key and your pinky finger on the A key. Your left thumb should be on the Space bar on the first row from the bottom. The Space bar is the longest key on the keyboard.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType># |a|s|d|f</TextToType>
		<LessonTime>2</LessonTime>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 3. Home Row - Both Hands</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>This lesson helps you practice using both hands on the Home row. Don't forget to place your fingers properly on the keyboard as you have managed very well in Lesson 1 and 2.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType>#a|s|d|f| |j|k|l|;</TextToType>
		<LessonTime>3</LessonTime>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 4. Home Row and Top Row - Right Hand</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>This is the practice exercise for your right hand on the Home row and the Top row. You should find the U key right above the J key, the I key above the K key, the O key above the L key and the P key above the Semi-colon key.
Tip: Use the respective five-finger position as you have learned from the previous lessons. For example, your index finger is used to type the J key on the Home row, then it is also used to type the U key above the J key; the middle finger is for the K and I keys... After you have finished typing a key on the Top row, your finger should find its way back to the Home row.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType># |j|u|k|i|l|o|;|p</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>3</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 5. Home Row and Top Row - Left Hand</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>This is the practice exercise for your left hand on the Home row and the Top row. You should find the R key right above the F key, the E key above the D key, the W key above the S key and the Q key above the A key.
Tip: Use the respective five-finger position as you have learned from the previous lessons. For example, your index finger is used to type the F key on the Home row, then it is also used to type the R key above the F key; the middle finger is for the D and E keys... After you have finished typing a key on the Top row, your finger should find its way back to the Home row.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType># |a|q|s|w|d|e|f|r</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>3</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
