	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 7. Home Row and Bottom Row - Right Hand</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>This is the practice exercise for your right hand on the Home row and the Bottom row. You should find the M key right below the J key, the Comma key below the K key, the Period key below the L key and the Forward Slash key below the Semi-conlon key.
Tip: Use the respective five-finger position as you have learned from the previous lessons. For example, your index finger is used to type the J key on the Home row, then it is also used to type the M key below the J key; the middle finger is for the K and Comma keys... After you have finished typing a key on the Bottom row, your finger should find its way back to the Home row.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType># |j|m|k|,|l|.|;|/</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>3</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 8. Home Row and Bottom Row - Left Hand</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>This is the practice exercise for your left hand on the Home row and the Bottom row. You should find the V key right below the F key, the C key below the D key, the X key below the S key and the Z key below the A key.
Tip: Use the respective five-finger position as you have learned from the previous lessons. For example, your index finger is used to type the F key on the Home row, then it is also used to type the V key below the F key; the middle finger is for the D and C keys... After you have finished typing a key on the Bottom row, your finger should find its way back to the Home row.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType># |a|z|s|x|d|c|f|v</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>3</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
