	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 10. Home Row - Index fingers</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>On the Home row, to the left of the J key, you will find the H key, and to the right of the F key, there is the G key. Use your right index finger to type H and your left index finger to type G.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType>#j|h|f|g</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>2</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 11. Home Row and Top Row - Index fingers</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>On the Top row, to the left of the U key, you will find the Y key, and to the right of the R key, there is the T key. In this lesson, you will practice using only the index fingers on both hands for the keys on the Home row and Top row.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType>#j|h|j|u|j|y|f|g|f|r|f|t</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>2</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 12. Home Row and Bottom Row - Index fingers</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>On the Bottom row, to the left of the M key, you will find the N key, and to the right of the V key, there is the B key. Use your right index finger to type M and N; and your left index finger to type V and B. In this lesson, you will practice using only the index fingers on both hands for the keys on the Home row and Bottom row.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType>#j|h|j|m|j|n|f|g|f|v|f|b</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>2</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 13. All Rows - Index fingers</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>In this lesson, you will practice using only the index fingers on both hands for the keys on all three rows, including the Home, Top and Bottom rows. Don't forget to use your left and right index fingers properly as you have managed very well in Lesson 10, 11 and 12.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType># |j|h|f|g|j|h|j|u|j|y|f|g|f|r|f|t|j|h|j|m|j|n|f|g|f|v|f|b</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>3</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 14. Numbers</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>Above the Top row, you will find the Number row. Use your left fingers respectively for the keys 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 as you have done with A, S, D, F, G and your right fingers for the keys 6, 7, 8, 9, 0 as you have done with H, J, K, L, Semi-colon.
In other words, you should use your left pinky finger to type 1, left ring to type 2, left middle to type 3, left index to type 4 and 5; right index to type 6 and 7, right middle to type 8, right ring to type 9 and right pinky to type 0. Please remember that after you have finished typing a key on other rows, your finger should always find its way back to the Home row. The Home row is used as the root to help you improve your typing speed and accuracy.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType># |a|1|s|2|d|3|f|4|g|5|h|6|j|7|k|8|l|9|;|0</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>4</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
	<Lesson>
		<Title>Lesson 15. Symbols on Home Row and Top Row</Title>
		<Author>Sao Mai Training Team</Author>
		<Description>In this lesson, you will practice using only your right pinky finger. On the Home row, to the right of the Semi-colon key, you will find the Single Quote key. On the Top row, to the right of the P key, there is the Left and the Right Bracket keys.
Press F2 to repeat the current full text to type, F3 to read the word to type, F4 to read the character to type and F5 to temporarily switch between different speaking as typing modes.</Description>
		<ExpectedPoint>85</ExpectedPoint>
		<TextToType>#;|'|;|p|;|[|;|]</TextToType>
		<ExpectedSpeed>40</ExpectedSpeed>
		<LessonTime>3</LessonTime>
	</Lesson>
